@remark **********************************************************************
@node introduction "Introduction"
@prev introduction
@next requirements
@toc main

  @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

    @{b}ACal@{ub} is a small utility which display a 'pretty' calendar on the
  @{b}Workbench@{ub} screen. It has been done for beeing displayed on @{b}MagicWB@{ub}
  screen :  it uses 8 colors brushes and the background color of the
  calendar window is the one used bu MagicCopper,  which allows you
  to show the copper list all around the calendar,  as if the window
  be transparent.

@endnode


@node requirements "Required configuration
@prev introduction
@next installation
@toc main

  @{b}@{u}Required configuration@{uu}@{ub}

  *  @{b}ACal@{ub} runs on every Amiga fitted with 2.04 + OS.
  *  I advise you own  @{b}MagicWB@{ub} or use a 8 or 16 colors Workbench.
  *  I you own WorkBench 2.1+,  @{b}ACal@{ub} will be localized. Internal
  language is french, but english & german catalogs are provided.
  *  You should have @{b}Installer@{ub} to run the installation program.
@endnode

@node installation "Installation"
@prev requirements
@next start
@toc main

  @{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}

  Double-click on the installation icon !!!
@endnode

@node start "Running"
@prev installation
@next menus
@toc main

  @{b}@{u}Running@{ub}@{uu}

  @{b}ACal@{ub} may be runned either from CLI or Workbench.

  If you have used the installation program, @{b}ACal@{ub} should be in 
  WBStartup  drawer and will be launched each time the computer reboots.

  CLI syntax is:

  ACal XPOS/K/N,YPOS/K/N,JFONT/K,SMFONT/K,LOCALE/K,BCOLOR/K
  
  where XPOS, YPOS, JFONT, SMFONT, LOCALE and BCOLOR match the icon @{"TOOLTYPES" link tooltypes}.
  
  If the program is launched from CLI, it first try to look at the
  TOOLTYPES and then to command line arguments. So these ones have priority
  on the TOOLTYPES.

@endnode

@node menus "ACal's menus"
@prev start
@next apropos
@toc main

  @{b}@{u}Menus@{ub}@{uu}

  Here is the list of menu items :

          @{b}Project@{ub}

            @{"About ...                  [?] " link apropos}
            --------------------------------
            @{"Quit                       [Q] " link quitter}


          @{b}Options@{ub}

            @{"Window to front            [F] " link pplan}
            @{"Window to back             [B] " link aplan}
            @{"  Lock window              [L] " link verrou}
            --------------------------------
            @{"Day font ...                   " link fjour}
            @{"Week/Month font ...            " link fsem}
            --------------------------------
            @{"Save preferences           [S] " link save}

@endnode

@node apropos "About ..."
@prev menus
@next quitter
@toc main

  @{b}@{u}About@{ub}@{uu}

  Displays a @{"Copyright" link copyright} window.
@endnode

@node quitter "Quit"
@prev apropos
@next pplan
@toc main

  @{b}@{u}Quit@{ub}@{uu}

  Ends the program.

  The program may also be ended by double clicking in the window when it is locked.
@endnode

@node pplan "Window to front"
@prev quitter
@next aplan
@toc main

  @{b}@{u}Window to front@{ub}@{uu}

  Puts the window in front of the others.
@endnode

@node aplan "Window to back"
@prev pplan
@next verrou
@toc main

  @{b}@{u}Window to back@{ub}@{uu}

  Puts the window behind the others.
@endnode

@node  verrou "Lock window"
@prev aplan
@next fjour
@toc main

  @{b}@{u}Lock window@{ub}@{uu}

  If this menu item is checked, the window can't be moved.
  This prevents you from moving the window accidently once you've
  positionned it with care and @{"saved the prefs" link save} to disk.

  To move the window, simply un-check this menu item.

@endnode

@node fjour "Day font"
@prev verrou
@next fsem
@toc main

  @{b}@{u}Day font@{ub}@{uu}

  Displays a font requester to choose the day of the month font.
@endnode

@node fsem "Week day/Month font"
@prev fjour
@next save
@toc main

  @{b}@{u}Week day/Month font@{ub}@{uu}

  Displays a font requester to choose the week day and the month font.
@endnode


@node save "Save preferences"
@prev fsem
@next tooltypes
@toc main

  @{b}@{u}Save preferences@{ub}@{uu}

  Allows you to save preferences :

  * window position,
  
  * Day font,
  
  * Week day/Month font.


  The preferences are saved in the @{"TOOLTYPES" link tooltypes} of the program
  icon. That way, there's no need for a prefs file in s: or elsewhere :-)
@endnode


@node tooltypes "TOOLTYPES"
@prev save
@next copyright
@toc main

  @{b}@{u}TOOLTYPES@{ub}@{uu}

  @{b}ACal@{ub} uses this tooltypes:
  
  * @{b}XPOS@{ub} and @{b}YPOS@{ub}    : Window position on the Workbench screen.
  
  * @{b}JFONT@{ub} and @{b}SMFONT@{ub} : Day and week day/month fonts.

    Fonts are named that way :
    
    <name><size>
    
    for instance, for times 18, people will write : ...FONT=times18 

  * @{b}LOCALE@{ub}                    : selects a locale different from the
                                         default one.

  * @{b}BCOLOR@{ub}                    : change background color.
@endnode
    

